      "note_no": "4",
      "note": "Lit., \"among the people there is he who [or \"such as\"] takes playful [or \"idle\"] talk in exchange\", i.e., for divine guidance: apparently an allusion to a pseudo-philosophical play with words and metaphysical speculations without any real meaning behind them (cf. note 38 on 23:67). Contrary to what some of the commentators assume, the above statement does not refer to any one person (allegedly a contemporary of the Prophet) but describes a type of mentality and has, therefore, a general import."
